<P>Sir Hugh was a ver&s;e to letting his nieces go abroad
again &s;o &s;oon: but Mi&s;s Margland, extremely anxious
about her own chance for the prize, &s;olemnly a&s;&s;erted
its nece&s;&s;ity; inveighed again&s;t the mi&s;management of
every thing at Cleves, &s;tifled all her complaints of
