<P>Dr. Marchmont was a man of the highe&s;t intel|lectual
accompli&s;hments, uniting deep learning with
general knowledge, and the graceful exterior of a
man of the world, with the $rudition and &s;cience of
a fellow of a coll$ge. He obtained the e&s;teem of the
&s;cholar where$$$ he was known, and caught the appro|bation
of the mo&s;t uncultivated wherever he was &s;een.</P>
<P>When the &s;e$$$ce was over, Edgar propo&s;ed that
